# Identity & Access Management (v1.0 — architecture revision)

## Principles

1. **Directory Contact** is the enterprise identity SSOT — every person exists as a Contact first  
2. **Never** create User Accounts directly — only via **Grant Platform Access** on a Contact  
3. Identity ≠ User Account ≠ Roles ≠ Permissions ≠ Platform Access  
4. Unlimited roles (responsibility); Effective Permission Set alone enforces access  
5. Formula: Roles → Role Permissions → Templates → User Overrides → Effective Set → Platform Access  
6. Login Status: Pending Invitation | Active | Suspended | Archived  
7. Platform Access on Contact: No Access | Catalyst One | COMPASS | Both (default No Access)  
8. Exit: deactivate login, retain Contact, transfer work, keep audit — never delete identity  
9. Super Admin last-active protections remain  

## Flow

Directory Contact → Grant Platform Access → User Account → Assign Roles → Effective Permissions

## Source of truth

- ECM Contact: `src/types/enterprise-contact-master.ts` (`platformAccess`, `linkedUserId`)  
- User Account: `src/types/enterprise-user-management.ts`  
- Effective engine: `src/lib/enterprise-user-management/effective-permissions.ts`  
- Grant/revoke: `src/lib/enterprise-user-management/iam-lifecycle.ts`  
- UI: Administration → Users; Directory employee action → Grant Access  
